[{"id":"VH979996","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two straight wires that are perpendicular to each other, wire 1 and wire 2, and each carry a current i. Wire 1 is horizontal, and i is directed to the right. Wire 2 is vertical, and i is directed upward. The point P is indicated and is a distance d vertically below the center of wire 1, and a distance 2 d horizontally to the left of the center of wire 2.\" height=\"263\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979996.g01.png\" width=\"350\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Wires 1 and 2 are distances <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 d\"><math alttext=\"2 d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> from point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The wires each have a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> in the directions shown. Which of the following is correct for the magnetic field at point P due to the current in the wires?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH979996_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Zero</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B equals, the fraction with numerator, mu sub 0, end sub, times i, and denominator 4 pi d\"><math alttext=\"B equals, the fraction with numerator, mu sub 0, end sub, times i, and denominator 4 pi d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>μ</mi><